glosses: to herd, tend, drive, shepherd, graze
to cherish, nourish (a grudge, an ambition, an aim)

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish كوتمك (gütmek), from Proto-Turkic *kǖt- (“to wait; to attend; to respect; to graze”).
Cognate with
Old Turkic [script needed] (kǖt-), [script needed] (küd-, “to wait, watch, graze”),
Kazakh күту (kütu, “to wait”),
Kyrgyz күтүү (kütüü, “to wait; to tend to (cattle)”),
Azerbaijani güdmək (“to graze”),
Bashkir көтөү (kötöw, “to wait, graze”),
Yakut күүт (küüt, “to wait”) / көһүт (köhüt, “to wait”), etc.
